<TITLE> Landslide kills 46 in north India </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MUMBAI, Aug 9 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - At least forty-six people were killed in a landslide triggered by heavy rains in the northern Indian state of Uttarakhand, police said on Sunday. Three villages in the hilly Pithoragarh district were swept away in the landslide after a cloudburst on Saturday, local police official M.S. Sathnam said. Seventeen bodies have so far been recovered, he said, with rescue efforts on Saturday by local emergency personnel and the Indo-Tibetan Border Police hampered by bad weather. "It has stopped raining now, and rescue work is underway in full swing," he said
